OL,3,C'Vital' bus service for cancer
OL,4,Cpatients found not to be 'best value
OL,5,Cfor money'
OL,7,FJersey health officials have defended
OL,8,Fending a #56,600 contract for a bus
OL,9,Fservice for cancer patients, citing
OL,10,Fdeclining service use and value for
OL,11,Fmoney.
OL,13,FThe Daisy Bus Service provides
OL,14,Ftransport for patients from Jersey and
OL,15,Fthe Isle of Wight travelling to the
OL,16,FUniversity Hospital Southampton for
OL,17,Fcancer treatment.
OL,19,FHowever, the NHS and Wessex Cancer
OL,20,FSupport have confirmed the service
OL,21,Fwill end on Wednesday 20 August.
