OL,3,C'Vital' bus service for cancer
OL,4,Cpatients found not to be 'best value
OL,5,Cfor money'
OL,7,FEmily Hoban, the Head of Access for
OL,8,FHCJ, stated: "A notable decline in
OL,9,FJersey patients using the service this
OL,10,Fyear meant that the Daisy Bus was
OL,11,Foperating at a cost of around #60 per
OL,12,Fpassenger journey.
OL,14,F"This is significantly higher than the
OL,15,Faverage cost of a #19 taxi journey.
OL,17,F"The termination of the Daisy Bus
OL,18,Fcontract will not impact Jersey
OL,19,Fpatients as all taxis are already
OL,20,Fbooked and paid for directly by HCJ's
OL,21,FTravel Office."
